== Secret Storage ==

The Secrets API allows client applications to store secrets securely using a service running in the user's login session.

=== Drafting Process ===
This API is currently being drafted in cooperation by the [[http://live.gnome.org/GnomeKeyring|GNOME Keyring]] and the [[http://utils.kde.org/projects/kwalletmanager|KDE Wallet]] developers. Everyone's welcome to join the discussion and drafting process on our [[http://lists.freedesktop.org/mailman/listinfo/Authentication|mailinglist]].

=== Mailinglist ===
Discussion of this specification should occur on the [[http://lists.freedesktop.org/mailman/listinfo/Authentication|Authentication mailing list]].

=== GIT ===
The specifiation draft is currently hosted on a Gitorious branch of the xdg-specs repository: [[http://gitorious.org/+xdg-secrets-api/xdg-specs/secrets-xdg-specs|xdg-secrets-api branch]].

